<div id="review_16380153" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/16380153" />
    <a title="Tyler" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/159142-tyler"><img alt="Tyler" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/16380153?book_show_action=true">Feb 25, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tyler" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tyler" href="/user/show/159142-tyler">Tyler</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/159142-tyler?shelf=notsopretentiousclassics">notsopretentiousclassics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer16380153" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11213318423062037707">read this book. i compare it somewhat to an arabian things fall apart (the oasis and seaside communities face drastic upheaval with the arrival of the western oilmen) but then also to an arabian faulkner-ite yoknapatawpha county - really the whole fictional country is the county - filled with a multitude of great characters with a story that meanders through the destruction of an oasis community to the gulf coast and the development of port city that rapidly grows sucking in money and workers an</span>
  <span id="freeText11213318423062037707" style="display:none">read this book. i compare it somewhat to an arabian things fall apart (the oasis and seaside communities face drastic upheaval with the arrival of the western oilmen) but then also to an arabian faulkner-ite yoknapatawpha county - really the whole fictional country is the county - filled with a multitude of great characters with a story that meanders through the destruction of an oasis community to the gulf coast and the development of port city that rapidly grows sucking in money and workers and all kinds of social upheaval. Its the first of 5 (although only 3 have been translated into english) and it gives a view of the arabian perspective of the oil economy (the author was an oil economist from saudi who had his citizenship revoked) and the west better than anything i've ever seen. If you're at all interested in saudi or other arab oil states, read this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11213318423062037707" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


