<div id="review_1720186782" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1720186782" />
    <a title="Dustin Hanvey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6038783-dustin-hanvey"><img alt="Dustin Hanvey" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1720186782?book_show_action=true">Aug 05, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dustin Hanvey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dustin Hanvey" href="/user/show/6038783-dustin-hanvey">Dustin Hanvey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1720186782" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6221396700256535151">Every once in a while in my experience, a book comes along that opens new possibilities and ways of viewing the world. Munif&apos;s novel for me is one of those books. Seemingly inspired by Chinua Achebe&apos;s Things Fall Apart, Cities Of Salt tells the story of the changes brought by globalization and the oil economy in an unnamed Middle Eastern society. Seeing this very complex and current issue from the perspective of the locals most affected by the changes was eye opening. I can see why the novel has</span>
  <span id="freeText6221396700256535151" style="display:none">Every once in a while in my experience, a book comes along that opens new possibilities and ways of viewing the world. Munif's novel for me is one of those books. Seemingly inspired by Chinua Achebe's Things Fall Apart, Cities Of Salt tells the story of the changes brought by globalization and the oil economy in an unnamed Middle Eastern society. Seeing this very complex and current issue from the perspective of the locals most affected by the changes was eye opening. I can see why the novel has been banned in many countries-- it hits on many very open wounds.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6221396700256535151" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


